@Mr.JoeArt 

inside your player movement script, create a bool canMove. in Update, wrap the rotate player and animate player walk functions in if(canMove). Do the same with DetectMovement in fixed update.

Create a reference to your player movement script within the character animation script. create 2 functions; DisableMovement and EnableMovement.

private PlayerMovement playerMovement;
void Awake()
    {
        anim = GetComponent<Animator>();
        playerMovement = GetComponentInParent<PlayerMovement>();
    }

 void DisableMovement()
    {
        playerMovement.canMove = false;
    }
void EnableMovement()
    {
        playerMovement.canMove = true;
    }

Finally, in your attack animations, create events to trigger the disable and enable movement functions (similar to enabling and disabling the attack points.
